song_name: Like It Love It Need It

version_description: This is the single song with chord placings tidied and put in correct places. Added because if you search for What Have We Become, there are no dc Talk results.
Original song is a semitone lower.

NOTE: I tried to space apart the chords to match the lyrics as Tori starts the chord first and then in many spots (noted with ), she sings the note on the 2nd beat (not 1st). Also note, original key is B minor and the time signature is 2/4 per bar except where noted (it will go to 3/4 temporarily before going back to 2/4).

From Tori Amos' 2017 album "Native Invader". Made much easier by playing in "G" on Capo 3 so you can still be in the correct key of the song. Tempo and strumming patterns should allow you to play along but do not match the acoustic guitar in the song, this is based off the piano. Edited to fix bridge after re-listening.
